definitions: Placed (a document or application) in a particular repository or among a collection of similar items.
Submitted (a legal document, application, or charge) to a court or other authority.
Walked in a line, one after another.
Sharpened, smoothed, or reduced with a file.
examples: She filed the papers in the cabinet.
The lawyer filed a motion with the court.
The students filed out of the classroom.
He filed down the rough edges of the wood.
